OL,6,FProf Ranger will say: "Treating
OL,7,Fpatients in corridors used to be an
OL,8,Fexceptional circumstance. Now it is a
OL,9,Fregular occurrence and a symptom of a
OL,10,Fsystem in crisis.
OL,12,F"We are right to be angry that this
OL,13,Fonce abnormal practice has become
OL,14,Fnormalised."
OL,16,FThe Welsh Government, which oversees
OL,17,Fhealth and social care in Wales, says
OL,18,Fit's investing #283million in the
OL,19,Feducation and training of healthcare
OL,20,Fprofessionals in Wales this year.
