OL,6,F"We have invested an extra #450million
OL,7,Ffor the NHS in addition to the
OL,8,F#425million which was announced in
OL,9,FOctober for the remainder of this
OL,10,Ffinancial year. This means that NHS in
OL,11,FWales will receive more than a 4%
OL,12,Fincrease for this year compared to
OL,13,Fless than 1% in England.
OL,15,F"We are also continuing to invest in
OL,16,Fthe NHS workforce and this year are
OL,17,Finvesting #281million to increase the
OL,18,Fnumber of training places to ensure
OL,19,Fthe NHS has the workforce it needs."
